OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,FMr Simons faced calls to resign after
OL,8,Fhis think tank, Labour Together, was
OL,9,Faccused of paying PR firm Apco
OL,10,FWorldwide #36,000 to investigate the
OL,11,Fbackground of journalists who had
OL,12,Fwritten stories about it.
OL,14,FIn previous statements, Mr Simons said
OL,15,FApco had been hired to investigate an
OL,16,Fillegal hack.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,FBut in a letter to the Prime Minister,
OL,8,Fethics adviser Sir Laurie Magnus said
OL,9,Fthe former minister now accepted the
OL,10,Fterms he agreed with Apco were "wider
OL,11,Fthan he had understood" and he had
OL,12,Facted "too hastily in confirming their
OL,13,Fappointment".
OL,15,FWhile Sir Laurie said Mr Simons had
OL,16,Facted "in good faith", he said the MP
OL,17,Facknowledged the "perceived gap
OL,18,Fbetween his public statements and what
OL,19,Fhe now accepts appears to be a more
OL,20,Fextensive scope has been damaging".
OL,26,@rD@`OUsD@WO]tD@GOUuD@LO]xD@GOUxD@UO]yD@
OL,26,AROU|D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,FSir Laurie added: "I see no basis for
OL,8,Fadvising you of any breach of the
OL,9,FMinisterial Code by Mr Simons but you
OL,10,Fwill wish to consider, in the light of
OL,11,Fthis distraction and potential
OL,12,Freputational damage, whether he
OL,13,Fcontinues to hold your confidence as a
OL,14,Fmember of your Government."
OL,16,FIn his letter to the Prime Minister Mr
OL,17,FSimons said he had "never sought to
OL,18,Fsmear (the) newspaper reporters" and
OL,19,Fhad "sought to investigate how
OL,20,Fconfidential material had been
OL,21,Fdisclosed".
OL,26,@oD@SOUvD@[O]zD@GpmzD@Kpn
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,FBut he said, it was "clear" he had
OL,8,Fbecome "a distraction".
OL,10,FHe said: "I welcome that Sir Laurie
OL,11,FMagnus has cleared me of breaching the
OL,12,FMinisterial Code. It was important to
OL,13,Fme to complete this process to prove
OL,14,Fthat I behaved with integrity and that
OL,15,Fmy public statements have been
OL,16,Ftruthful and honest.
OL,18,F"Nonetheless, it is clear that my
OL,19,Fremaining in office has now become a
OL,20,Fdistraction from this Government's
OL,21,Fimportant work.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,F"For that reason, and with sadness and
OL,8,Fregret, I offer my resignation. It has
OL,9,Fbeen an honour to serve this great
OL,10,Fcountry."
OL,12,FSir Keir said he had accepted "with
OL,13,Fsadness" the resignation, adding he
OL,14,Frespected his decision.
OL,16,F"I want to express my thanks for the
OL,17,Fcommitment, focus, and energy you have
OL,18,Fbrought to ministerial office," he
OL,19,Fsaid in his reply to Mr Simons' letter
OL,20,Fof resignation.
OL,26,@tD@_OUuD@HO]xD@AOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,FSir Keir added: "In accepting your
OL,8,Fresignation, I also want to place on
OL,9,Frecord that the Independent Adviser,
OL,10,FSir Laurie Magnus, found no breach of
OL,11,Fthe Ministerial Code. I am grateful
OL,12,Ffor your full and proactive
OL,13,Fcooperation throughout his work.
OL,15,F"I understand that, to avoid any
OL,16,Fongoing distraction from delivering
OL,17,Fthe Government's mission, you have
OL,18,Ftaken the difficult decision to step
OL,19,Faside.
OL,26,@oD@QOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1772374275
OL,3,CCabinet Office minister Josh Simons
OL,4,Cresigns over Labour Together
OL,5,C'distraction'
OL,7,F"I respect that decision, and I look
OL,8,Fforward to continuing to work with you
OL,9,Fin driving forward the Government's
OL,10,Fpriorities."
OL,12,FHave you heard our podcast Talking
OL,13,FPolitics? Tom and Robert dig into the
OL,14,Fbiggest issues dominating the
OL,15,Fpolitical agenda in every episode...
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@LO]
